<p>Received 25 May 1940</p>

<p>MOST SECRET</p>

<p>I have read with much interest your telegram of the 22nd May. [1] I concur in your view as to the gravity of the situation and importance of any aid that can be secured from the United States.</p>

<p>I was about to reply when I received a copy of Mr. Churchillâ€™s telegram to you. [2] I have just sent Mr. Churchill a reply which indicates that I concur in his view of the situation. I appreciate the full exposition of your views and shall be glad at any time to discuss the most effective means of advancing the common cause in this difficult hour.</p>

<p>My reply to Mr. Churchill follows.</p>

